name: Sheela Restaurant & Bar

reviews.review_text: Great place for local food, fresh fish done well in both red & green paste. I had surmai & lepo fry & both were done well. The place has decently good ambience for a local joint. Highly recommend if one is close to dabolim airport & looking for a good place to eat.

We had a family lunch twice in one month and the food was simply delicious. Great service. It was monsoons and we had a security coming to the vehicle to pick us up with an umbrella I’ve never had this experience in Goa being a Goan. We enjoyed ❤️

Really amazed by the quality of food served. Every dish I ordered was absolutely delicious
Ox(Reality Beef) tongue roast was just awesomeeeeeee.
I ordered a couple of mocktails and starters, followed by mixed and prawn fried rice.

description:
### Discovering Sheela Restaurant & Bar: A Goan Gem

Nestled conveniently near Goa's Dabolim Airport, **Sheela Restaurant & Bar** has captivated diners with an impressive **4-star rating** based on **4,664 reviews**. Renowned for its authentic local cuisine, this establishment boasts culinary highlights such as **pork**, **fish thali**, and a delightful **caramel custard**, making it a sought-after destination for both locals and visitors alike.

### A Welcoming Ambiance

Step inside Sheela Restaurant & Bar, and you'll immediately notice its charming ambiance that blends comfort and local flair. Photos reveal a cozy yet vibrant setting, adorned with simple décor that reflects Goan culture. The lighting strikes a perfect balance—inviting enough for a family dinner, yet casual enough for a quick bite after a day of exploration. The overall atmosphere is enhanced by the cheerful chatter of satisfied diners, fostering a friendly and welcoming environment.

### A Culinary Odyssey

The menu at Sheela is a testament to the region's rich culinary heritage. Reviewers frequently rave about the **fresh fish**, expertly prepared in both **red and green paste**, as highlighted in one patron's experience with **surmai** and **lepo fry**—a testament to the kitchen's dedication to quality. There’s also enthusiasm for the unsung hero of the menu, the **Ox Tongue Roast**, which one guest proclaimed to be “just awesomeeeeeee.” 

Diners can expect an intriguing range of options, from mixed rice dishes to prawn fried rice, all served with impeccable presentation. Vegetarians and those seeking dietary options will find satisfying choices, ensuring there is something for everyone.

### Exceptional Customer Care

The service at Sheela Restaurant & Bar stands out as much as the food itself. Patrons have noted the exceptional friendliness and attentiveness of the staff, going as far as to describe receiving service akin to luxury dining, complete with a staff member escorting guests to their vehicles with an umbrella during the rainy season. These personal touches, coupled with efficiency in service, have left many satisfied diners eager to return.

### Noteworthy Popularity

The positive buzz surrounding Sheela Restaurant & Bar is palpable across various platforms. The restaurant has developed a loyal following, with many guests sharing their delightful experiences on social media. The combination of great food, memorable service, and strategic location near the airport makes it a preferred spot for travelers looking to savor true Goan flavors.

### Visual Highlights

The imagery shared by customers captures the essence of Sheela beautifully. Each photo tells a story—whether it's the vibrant plating of a fish thali or the enticing sight of caramel custard awaiting a spoonful. The lush presentation of their dishes not only tantalizes the taste buds but also appeals to the eyes, inviting guests to indulge in a complete sensory experience.

### Conclusion

In summary, Sheela Restaurant & Bar is a must-visit establishment for anyone seeking authentic Goan cuisine with a side of wonderful hospitality. With its welcoming ambiance, delightful menu, and stellar service, it has rightfully earned its place on the culinary map of Goa. Whether you're just passing through or planning a longer stay, make sure to stop by for a meal that promises to be both memorable and delicious.
